# stockpile.csv.example
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Complete example of the stockpile manual transaction format.
# Every action type is shown. Copy this file to input/my-portfolio.csv
# and replace these rows with your own transactions.
#
# Lines starting with # are comments — ignored by every tool.
# Blank lines are also ignored.
#
# Prices are approximate historical figures as of the transaction date
# and are for illustration only.
#
# SIGN CONVENTION:
#   amount positive (+) = money you received  (selling, dividends)
#   amount negative (-) = money you paid      (buying shares or options)
#
# price is per share (or per underlying share for options, i.e. multiply
# by 100 for the value of one contract).
# If you leave amount blank the tool computes it from price × qty (± fees).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

date,action,symbol,quantity,option_type,strike,expiration,price,fees,amount,description

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AAPL — 120 shares held; 1 open covered call at $310
# (AAPL current ~$295)
# Demonstrates: BUY, DIVIDEND, SELL, STO, EXPIRED, BTC (roll)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# BUY — purchase shares (you paid, so amount is negative)
2024-01-15,BUY,AAPL,100,,,,,0.65,-18400.65,Initial position at ~$184

2025-03-01,BUY,AAPL,50,,,,,0.65,-11400.65,Adding at ~$228

# DIVIDEND — total cash received goes in amount; quantity is not needed
2025-06-01,DIVIDEND,AAPL,,,,,,,30.00,Quarterly dividend

# SELL — partial exit (you received, so amount is positive)
2025-07-01,SELL,AAPL,30,,,,,0.65,6329.35,Trimming at ~$211

# STO — sell a covered call OTM; premium received = positive amount
# AAPL was ~$215 when opened; $230 strike is ~7% OTM
2025-07-15,STO,AAPL,1,CALL,230.00,2025-10-17,3.50,0.65,349.35,Covered call

# EXPIRED — call expires worthless; price = 0, amount = 0
2025-10-17,EXPIRED,AAPL,1,CALL,230.00,2025-10-17,0.00,0.00,0.00,Expired worthless

# ROLL = two rows on the same day: BTC closes the old leg, STO opens new
# AAPL ~$255; $275 strike is ~8% OTM
2026-01-12,STO,AAPL,1,CALL,275.00,2026-06-19,4.20,0.65,419.35,Covered call

# BTC — buy to close (you paid, so amount is negative)
2026-03-20,BTC,AAPL,1,CALL,275.00,2026-06-19,1.10,0.65,-110.65,Roll — BTC leg

# STO — open the new leg on the same date as the BTC above
# AAPL ~$280; $310 strike is ~11% OTM — currently open
2026-03-20,STO,AAPL,1,CALL,310.00,2026-09-18,3.80,0.65,379.35,Roll — new leg (open)

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TSLA — 100 shares from a put assignment
# (TSLA current ~$433)
# Demonstrates: STO (CSP), ASSIGNED (2-row event)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# STO — sell a cash-secured put; TSLA was ~$380, $320 put is ~16% OTM
2025-04-01,STO,TSLA,1,PUT,320.00,2025-10-17,6.50,0.65,649.35,Cash-secured put

# ASSIGNED — short put gets assigned at expiration: always two rows.
# Row 1: close the option at $0
2025-10-17,ASSIGNED,TSLA,1,PUT,320.00,2025-10-17,0.00,0.00,0.00,Put assigned

# Row 2: record the shares you received (strike × 100 per contract)
2025-10-17,BUY,TSLA,100,,,,,0.00,-32000.00,Shares from put assignment at $320

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# MSFT — 50 shares; long call bought and sold for a profit
# (MSFT current ~$408)
# Demonstrates: BTO (long option), STC
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

2024-06-01,BUY,MSFT,50,,,,,0.65,-19400.65,Initial position at ~$388

# BTO — buy a long LEAPS call (you paid, so amount is negative)
# MSFT ~$395; $430 call is ~9% OTM
2025-01-15,BTO,MSFT,1,CALL,430.00,2027-01-15,14.50,0.65,-1450.65,Long LEAPS call

# STC — sell to close the long call for a profit (you received)
2025-11-20,STC,MSFT,1,CALL,430.00,2027-01-15,26.00,0.65,2599.35,Closed for profit

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AMD — 200 shares acquired by exercising long calls
# (AMD current ~$448)
# Demonstrates: BTO (long option), EXERCISED (2-row event)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# BTO — buy 2 long call contracts; AMD ~$280, $310 call is ~11% OTM
2025-01-10,BTO,AMD,2,CALL,310.00,2027-01-15,11.80,1.30,-2361.30,Long LEAPS calls

# EXERCISED — exercise a long option: always two rows.
# Row 1: close the option contracts
2025-12-05,EXERCISED,AMD,2,CALL,310.00,2027-01-15,0.00,0.00,0.00,Exercised

# Row 2: buy the shares at the strike (2 contracts × 100 shares = 200 shares)
2025-12-05,BUY,AMD,200,,,,,0.00,-62000.00,Shares from call exercise at $310

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SPY — protective puts bought then expired worthless
# (SPY current ~$738)
# Demonstrates: BTO (long put), EXPIRED (long side)
# Note: SPY has no shares, so it will NOT appear in the portfolio scan.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# BTO — buy puts for downside protection; SPY ~$700, $640 put is ~9% OTM
2025-06-01,BTO,SPY,5,PUT,640.00,2026-01-16,9.80,3.25,-4903.25,Protective puts

# EXPIRED — long puts expire worthless; you lose the premium paid
2026-01-16,EXPIRED,SPY,5,PUT,640.00,2026-01-16,0.00,0.00,0.00,Puts expired worthless

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NVDA — transferred in, then split
# (NVDA current ~$221)
# Demonstrates: TRANSFER_IN, SPLIT
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# TRANSFER_IN — shares arrived from another broker with no cost basis.
# Add the original BUY rows if you can find them; the tracker will flag
# this position as Inconsistent until you do.
2024-03-01,TRANSFER_IN,NVDA,20,,,,,,,Transferred from old broker (pre-split shares)

# SPLIT — additional shares from NVDA's 10:1 split in June 2024.
# quantity = number of ADDITIONAL shares (not the new total).
# 20 shares × 10:1 = 200 total; so 180 additional shares received.
2024-06-10,SPLIT,NVDA,180,,,,,,,10:1 split — 180 additional shares at $0
